%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWe%20are%20now%20rekindling%20our%20friendship%20and%20making%20up%20for%20lost%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20remember%20it%2C%20but%20I've%20been%20told%20Rebecca%20first%20approached%20me%20at%20orientation%20at%20Cottonwood%20Preschool%20in%20Littleton%2C%20Colorado.%20She%20walked%20right%20up%20to%20me%20and%20asked%20me%20to%20be%20her%20friend.%20As%20the%20kind%2C%20empathetic%20person%20I%20am%2C%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BNo.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20feel%20horrible%20about%20it%20to%20this%20day.%20To%20give%20myself%20credit%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fwhat-is-anxiety%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20have%20anxiety%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20that%20unfortunate%20interaction%20didn't%20actually%20stop%20us%20from%20being%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20that%20moment%20on%2C%20we%20became%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcelebrities-who-have-been-friends-since-they-were-kids%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildhood%20best%20friends%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20now%20we%20are%20trying%20to%20rekindle%20that%20friendship%20in%20college.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20were%20inseparable%20growing%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20parents%20first%20set%20us%20up%20on%20playdates%2C%20we%20became%20inseparable.%20We%20could%20make%20each%20other%20laugh%20about%20the%20most%20random%20things%20until%20we%20started%20crying.%20We%20loved%20to%20be%20in%20the%20spotlight%2C%20dancing%20ballet%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Nutcracker%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eevery%20year%20%E2%80%94%20making%20sure%20we%20knew%20all%20the%20parts.%20We%20loved%20performing%20overly%20dramatic%20karaoke%20songs%20for%20Rebecca's%20mom%20for%20hours.%20We%20ordered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-happy-meal-history-photos-2019-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcDonald's%20Happy%20Meals%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20kept%20the%20pickles%20on%20my%20cheeseburger%20to%20give%20them%20to%20her.%20We%20shared%20secrets%20and%20thoughts%20we%20didn't%20tell%20anyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20a%20connection%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsex-relationships%2Fplatonic-relationship%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplatonic%20soulmates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20dramatic%20as%20it%20sounds.%20Being%20around%20her%20didn't%20take%20any%20effort%2C%20and%20we%20never%20ran%20out%20of%20things%20to%20do%20or%20talk%20about.%20We%20could%20find%20joy%20in%20the%20smallest%20activities%2C%20from%20dressing%20up%20in%20her%20thrifted%20adult%20gown%20collection%20that%20drowned%20us%20in%20fabric%20to%20listening%20to%20her%20mom%20sing%20%26quot%3BDream%20a%20Little%20Dream%20of%20Me%26quot%3B%20to%20us%20as%20we%20fell%20asleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20the%20sister%20I%20never%20had%2C%20and%20I%20couldn't%20imagine%20my%20life%20without%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20as%20we%20got%20older%2C%20our%20relationship%20changed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20continued%20with%20ballet%20lessons%2C%20I%20stopped%20loving%20it%20as%20much%20as%20she%20did.%20I%20always%20enjoyed%20singing%20and%20wanted%20to%20try%20musical%20theater%2C%20but%20with%20ballet%20training%20five%20days%20a%20week%2C%20there%20wasn't%20time%20for%20both.%20So%2C%20I%20said%20goodbye%20to%20ballet%20at%2013%20and%20switched%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fliving-working-cruise-ship-job-performer-what-its-like-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emusical%20theater%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Rebecca%20kept%20dancing.%20It%20wasn't%20easy%20to%20keep%20in%20touch%20when%20we%20didn't%20go%20to%20the%20same%20school%2C%20couldn't%20drive%20ourselves%2C%20and%20were%20always%20busy%20with%20separate%20rehearsals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20tried%20to%20catch%20up%2C%20grabbing%20dinner%20here%20and%20there%20with%20our%20moms%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20how%20it%20used%20to%20be.%20We%20were%20navigating%20the%20end%20of%20middle%20and%20beginning%20of%20high%20school%20without%20each%20other%20%E2%80%94%20a%20pivotal%20moment%20of%20development%2C%20and%20our%20lives%20didn't%20align.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20barely%20spoke%20until%20we%20didn't%20at%20all.%20It%20felt%20like%20we%20couldn't%20connect%20in%20the%20same%20way%20that%20we%20used%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20are%20now%20getting%20a%20second%20chance%20at%20friendship%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20graduated%20from%20high%20school%20during%20the%20start%20of%20the%20pandemic%20in%202020%20when%20Rebecca%20was%20still%20a%20junior.%20Our%20contact%20was%20still%20minimal%2C%20but%20for%20my%20graduation%20present%2C%20she%20gifted%20me%20the%20sweetest%2C%20heartfelt%20gift.%20She%20put%20together%20a%20basket%20of%20items%20I%20loved%20and%20a%20thick%20stack%20of%20envelopes%20with%20prompts%20like%20%26quot%3BOpen%20me%20when%20you're%20sad%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BOpen%20me%20when%20you're%20missing%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20always%20a%20thoughtful%20gift-giver%2C%20but%20it%20meant%20so%20much%20that%20she%20still%20knew%20me%20after%20years%20of%20little%20interaction.%20I%20felt%20melancholic%20opening%20each%20envelope%20at%20Emerson%20College%2C%20sifting%20through%20her%20notes%20and%20photos%20she%20included%20of%20the%20little%2C%20happy%20girls%20we%20used%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERebecca%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-left-adult-injured-son-move-across-the-country-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoved%20to%20California%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20her%20parents%20after%20high%20school.%20But%20in%20a%20strange%20twist%20of%20fate%2C%20her%20college%20took%20away%20their%20film%20program%2C%20and%20she%20transferred%20to%20Emerson%20last%20fall.%20I%20was%20excited%20to%20see%20her%20again%2C%20but%20I%20was%20so%20nervous%20that%20it%20would%20feel%20weird.%20I%20worried%20that%20we%20would%20be%20stuck%20reminiscing%20and%20not%20growing%20our%20friendship%20as%20it%20exists%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomehow%2C%20when%20I%20first%20saw%20her%20at%20the%20Boylston%20T%20stop%20by%20our%20campus%2C%20my%20apprehensions%20faded%2C%20and%20it%20felt%20like%20we%20were%20never%20apart.%20She%20smiled%20at%20me%2C%20and%20I%20knew%20we%20would%20be%20OK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20both%20busy%20with%20classes%20and%20work%2C%20but%20we%20see%20each%20other%20at%20least%20once%20a%20week%20now.%20We%20attend%20movies%20with%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fstreaming%2Famc-a-list-tips-tricks-price-features%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAMC%20A-List%20passes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20hang%20out%20in%20her%20dorm%20room%2C%20get%20work%20done%2C%20or%20just%20chat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20I%20catch%20a%20glimmer%20of%20the%20little%20girls%20we%20used%20to%20be%20%E2%80%94%20in%20our%20giggles%20at%20jokes%20no%20one%20else%20understands%20or%20when%20we%20catch%20a%20Boston%20Ballet%20performance%20and%20debrief%20afterward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20often%20that%20you%20find%20someone%20you%20can%20be%20apart%20from%20for%20a%20long%20time%20and%20simply%20pick%20up%20where%20you%20left%20off%20when%20you%20reconnect%20again%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20when%20you%20met%20at%20a%20different%20stage%20of%20life%20than%20where%20you%20are%20now.%20But%20Rebecca%20is%20that%20person%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildhood-best-friend-lost-touch-reconnect-college-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708787281000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65d767fcf533b039a885f234%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildhood-