the%20streets%2C%20staging%20demonstrations%20outside%20government%20offices%20across%20the%20state.%20They%20have%20demanded%20a%20fresh%20police%20constable%20examination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aspirants%2C%20cutting%20across%20castes%20and%20religion%2C%20also%20staged%20a%20massive%20protest%20outside%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Public%20Service%20Commission%20office%20in%20Prayagraj%2C%20putting%20the%20BJP%20government%20in%20a%20tight%20corner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Govt%E2%80%99s%20denial%20mode%2C%20even%20after%20an%20aspirant%20filed%20an%20FIR%20alleging%20paper%20leak%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Lucknow%2C%20thousands%20of%20aspirants%20gathered%20to%20protest%20at%20the%20Eco%20Garden.%20They%20chanted%2C%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CEk%20hi%20nara%2C%20ek%20hi%20naam%2C%20re-exam%2C%20re-exam%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20a%20witty%20improvisation%20of%20the%20popular%20Hindutva%20slogan%20of%20the%20Sangh%20%3Cem%3Eparivar%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CEk%20hi%20nara%2C%20ek%20hi%20naam%2C%20Jai%20Shri%20Ram%2C%20Jai%20Shri%20Ram.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20slogan%20raised%20by%20the%20aspirants%20was%20a%20commentary%20on%20the%20current%20affairs%20of%20politics%20in%20the%20state%20where%20welfare%20issues%20are%20playing%20against%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Hindutva%20agenda%20ahead%20of%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20initially%20denying%20the%20allegations%20of%20a%20paper%20leak%2C%20the%20UP%20home%20department%2C%20under%20chief%20minister%20Adityanath%2C%20on%20Saturday%20afternoon%2C%20said%20it%20had%20directed%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Police%20Recruitment%20and%20Promotion%20Board%20(UPPRPB)%20to%20conduct%20fresh%20exams%20within%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20leak%20allegations%20would%20be%20probed%20by%20the%20UP%20Police%20Special%20Task%20Force.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2019%2C%20a%20police%20constable%20in%20Lucknow%20had%20lodged%20a%20first%20information%20report%20(FIR)%20over%20a%20paper%20leak%20in%20his%20exam%20centre%2C%20within%20hours%20after%20the%20two-day%20exam%20ended.%20Despite%20that%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20top%20leadership%20and%20officials%20continued%20to%20deny%20the%20allegations%20of%20paper%20leak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20FIR%2C%20which%20says%20that%20around%20150%20questions%20that%20were%20found%20in%20a%20paper%20chit%2C%20carried%20by%20an%20accused%20applicant%20to%20the%20exam%20centre%2C%20were%20featured%20in%20the%20question%20paper%2C%20indicating%20that%20the%20paper%20had%20been%20leaked%20in%20advance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2023%2C%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20Keshav%20Prasad%20Maurya%20dismissed%20the%20allegations%20of%20paper%20leak%2C%20attributing%20it%20to%20an%20agenda%20by%20the%20Samajwadi%20Party%20(SP)%2C%20and%20said%20that%20he%20had%20no%20information%20of%20any%20such%20irregularities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeparately%2C%20a%20delegation%20of%20seven%20students%20met%20the%20UPPRPB%20director%20general%2C%20Renuka%20Mishra%2C%20and%20gave%20her%20a%20memorandum%20of%20demands.%20However%2C%20she%20did%20not%20openly%20admit%20to%20the%20paper%20leak.%20She%20said%20that%20the%20board%20was%20examining%20the%20applications%20of%20complaints%20sent%20on%20email%20by%20the%20aspirants%20who%20had%20alleged%20a%20paper%20leak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20on%20the%20days%20of%20the%20examination%20on%20February%2017%20and%2018%2C%20the%20UPPRPB%20dismissed%20any%20paper%20leak%20allegations%2C%20saying%20that%20a%20preliminary%20probe%20found%20out%20that%20some%20%E2%80%9Canti-social%20elements%E2%80%9D%20had%20spread%20the%20rumour%20of%20a%20paper%20leak%20on%20social%20media%20after%20tampering%20with%20a%20document%20through%20the%20edit%20option%20on%20the%20Telegram%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20as%20the%20allegations%20kept%20pouring%20in%20and%20aspirants%20started%20raising%20objections%20on%20social%20media%2C%20the%20UPPRPB%2C%20on%20February%2018%2C%20after%20the%20written%20tests%20were%20concluded%2C%20said%20it%20would%20%E2%80%9Cthoroughly%20verify%E2%80%9D%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunverified%20news%E2%80%9D%20that%20was%20trending%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20midst%20of%20the%20protests%2C%20the%20UPPRPB%20asked%20aspirants%20to%20submit%20evidence%20regarding%20the%20purported%20paper%20leak%20by%20the%20evening%20of%20February%2023.%20They%20assured%20protesters%20that%20they%20would%20thoroughly%20examine%20the%20witnesses%20and%20evidence%20provided%2C%20and%20take%20subsequent%20action%20based%20on%20their%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20Opposition%20parties%2C%20including%20the%20SP%20and%20the%20Congress%2C%20strongly%20backing%20the%20agitating%20aspirants%20during%20their%20protest%2C%20the%20cancellation%20of%20the%20constable%20recruitment%20exam%20has%20left%20the%20BJP%20government%2C%20which%20wanted%20to%20showcase%20its%20record%20of%20job%20creation%20before%20the%20election%2C%20red-faced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20damage-control%20measure%2C%20the%20government%20has%20said%20that%20whenever%20the%20exams%20are%20held%20again%2C%20the%20aspirants%20would%20be%20provided%20free%20transportation%20on%20the%20state-run%20buses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Adityanath%20government%20has%20instructed%20the%20UPPRPB%2C%20which%20is%20headed%20by%20a%20top%20IPS%20officer%2C%20to%20find%20out%20at%20what%20level%20the%20negligence%20took%20place%20and%20to%20lodge%20an%20FIR%20against%20the%20guilty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20said%20it%20cancelled%20the%20examination%20after%20scrutinising%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfacts%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cinformation%E2%80%9D%20of%20irregularities%2C%20aiming%20to%20maintain%20%E2%80%9Ctransparency%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Csanctity%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20exams.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdityanath%20said%20that%20tough%20action%20would%20be%20taken%20against%20the%20individuals%20and%20institutes%20found%20guilty%20in%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnother%20case%20of%20paper%20leak%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20also%20initiated%20a%20probe%20into%20the%20recently%20held%20examinations%20for%20the%20posts%20of%20Review%20Officers%20and%20Assistant%20Review%20Officers%20(February%2011)%20and%20sought%20complaints%20by%20aspirants%20till%20February%2027.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Police%20Constable%20Recruitment%20Examination%202023%20was%20conducted%20in%20almost%202%2C400%20centres%20across%20the%20state.%20From%20February%2015%20to%2018%2C%20the%20state%20police%2C%20including%20the%20UP%20STF%2C%20said%20they%20arrested%20or%20detained%20at%20least%20244%20persons%20on%20charges%20of%20cheating%20in%20the%20examination%2C%20impersonating%20candidates%20for%20money%2C%20defrauding%20candidates%20by%20promising%20them%20success%2C%20and%20duping%20aspirants%20with%20the%20promise%20of%20leaking%20the%20paper%20to%20them.%20The%20arrests%20continued%20even%20after%20the%20conclusion%20of%20the%20exams.%20As%20of%20now%2C%20there%20is%20no%20confirmed%20final%20tally%20of%20the%20number%20of%20arrests%20made%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20those%20arrested%20were%20an%20Indian%20Navy%20deserter%20Monu%20Gurjar%20(from%20Shamli)%2C%20who%20had%20allegedly%20tried%20to%20manipulate%20the%20exam%3B%20Anjani%20Kumar%2C%20a%20station%20master%20at%20the%20Singhiyaghat%20railway%20station%20in%20neighbouring%20Bihar%2C%20who%20allegedly%20sat%20in%20the%20exam%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Csolver%E2%80%9D%20in%20place%20of%20a%20candidate%20from%20Gorakhpur%3B%20an%20exam%20invigilator%20in%20Basti%2C%20who%20was%20allegedly%20caught%20tutoring%20candidates%3B%20and%20a%20former%20pradhan%20in%20Ghazipur%20district%2C%20who%20was%20part%20of%20a%20gang%20of%20manipulators.%20The%20police%20also%20arrested%20some%20people%20for%20allegedly%20spreading%20rumours%20that%20the%20paper%20had%20been%20leaked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2023%2C%20Sanyukt%20Yuva%20Morcha%2C%20a%20forum%20for%20youth%20organisations%2C%20wrote%20to%20chief%20minister%20Adityanath%2C%20demanding%20that%20the%20cases%20lodged%20against%20the%20aspirants%20for%20criticising%20the%20government%20over%20the%20paper%20leak%20or%20for%20providing%20information%20about%20the%20lapse%20be%20withdrawn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20in%20February%2C%20Adityanath%20informed%20the%20state%20assembly%20that%20the%20BJP%20government%20had%20recruited%201.55%20lakh%20police%20personnel%2C%20including%2022%2C670%20women%2C%20ever%20since%20it%20came%20to%20power.%20The%20last%20main%20recruitment%20was%20conducted%20in%202019%2C%20when%20examinations%20to%20fill%2049%2C568%20posts%20of%20civil%20and%20armed%20police%20personnel%20were%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20does%20the%20FIR%20say%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20FIR%20in%20the%20paper%20leak%20case%20was%20lodged%20at%20Krishna%20Nagar%20police%20station%20in%20Lucknow%20on%20February%2019%20at%20midnight%2C%20based%20on%20the%20complaint%20of%20constable%20Rambabu%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20case%20was%20registered%20under%20Section%20420%20(cheating)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%20Section%2066D%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20Act%2C%20and%20Sections%203%20and%2010%20of%20the%20UP%20Public%20Examination%20(Prevention%20of%20Unfair%20Means)%20Act%2C%201998%2C%20against%20one%20candidate%20Satya%20Aman%20Kumar%20and%20an%20alleged%20racketter%20Neeraj%20Kumar%2C%20who%2C%20according%20to%20the%20police%2C%20provided%20Aman%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20questions%20before%20the%20exam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20matter%20came%20to%20light%20when%20constable%20Ram%20Babu%20was%20informed%20by%20two%20invigilators%20at%20the%20City%20Modern%20Academy%20exam%20centre%20that%20a%20candidate%20was%20caught%20filling%20the%20OMR%20sheet%20with%20an%20illegal%20paper%20chit%20in%20his%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20tallying%20the%20chit%20with%20the%20question%20paper%2C%20the%20constable%20found%20that%20the%20questions%20were%20identical.%20Aman%20Kumar%E2%80%99s%20phone%20was%20inspected%20and%20it%20was%20found%20that%20Neeraj%20had%20sent%20him%20the%20correct%20answers%20on%20a%20paper%20through%20WhatsApp%20before%20the%20exam.%20Aman%20allegedly%20prepared%20the%20chit%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20paper%20that%20Neeraj%20sent%20to%20him%2C%20said%20the%20FIR.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20three%20SP%20MLAs%2C%20Atul%20Pradhan%2C%20Ragini%20Sonker%2C%20and%20Pinki%20Yadav%2C%20and%20one%20RLD%20MLA%2C%20Persann%20Kumar%2C%20had%20written%20to%20Adityanath%20saying%20that%20some%20aspirants%20from%20their%20constituency%20had%20informed%20them%20that%20the%20paper%20had%20been%20leaked%20on%20mobile%20phone%20and%20social%20media%20apps%2C%20much%20before%20the%20scheduled%20examination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Big%20victory%20for%20student%20power%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20the%20cancellation%20of%20the%20exam%2C%20SP%20chief%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%20said%20the%20decision%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cvictory%20of%20the%20youth%20and%20the%20defeat%20of%20the%20machinations%20of%20the%20BJP%20government.%E2%80%9D%20Yadav%20alleged%20that%20since%20the%20BJP%20government%20had%20earlier%20denied%20the%20paper%20leak%2C%20their%20admission%20now%20meant%20that%20the%20officers%20and%20criminals%20were%20in%20collusion%20and%20that%20they%20enjoyed%20the%20blessings%20of%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20in%20the%20face%20of%20all%20the%20evidence%2C%20the%20government%20has%20been%20forced%20to%20bow%20down%20to%20avoid%20a%20historic%20defeat%20in%20the%20elections%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Yadav%2C%20who%20had%20strongly%20backed%20the%20protests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20chief%20minister%20demanded%20that%20the%20BJP%20government%20return%20the%20fees%20collected%20by%20it%20through%20form%20submission%2C%20wondering%20if%20the%20huge%20sum%20running%20into%20crores%20would%20go%20into%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20election%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNow%20everyone%20has%20started%20to%20understand%20the%20truth%20of%20the%20game%20that%20the%20BJP%20government%20is%20playing%20with%20unemployed%20young%20men%20and%20women%20in%20the%20name%20of%20jobs.%20First%20they%20announce%20job%20vacancies%20for%20show%2C%20charge%20fees%20worth%20billions%20of%20rupees%2C%20allow%20the%20papers%20to%20be%20leaked%20and%20then%20pretend%20to%20cancel%20them%E2%80%A6%20this%20game%20will%20prove%20very%20costly%20for%20BJP%20this%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Yadav.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20who%20has%20been%20vocal%20in%20supporting%20the%20demands%20of%20the%20candidates%20during%20his%20Nyay%20Yatra%20in%20UP%2C%20said%20the%20cancellation%20of%20the%20exam%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbig%20victory%20for%20student%20power%20and%20unity%20of%20the%20youth.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20message%20is%20clear%20%E2%80%93%20no%20matter%20how%20much%20the%20government%20tries%20to%20suppress%20the%20truth%2C%20our%20rights%20can%20be%20won%20only%20by%20fighting%20unitedly.%20Those%20who%20unite%20will%20win%2C%20those%20who%20divide%20will%20be%20crushed%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Gandhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20sister%20Priyanka%20Gandhi-Vadra%2C%20who%20had%20demanded%20a%20CBI%20probe%20into%20the%20paper%20leak%2C%20said%20the%20leak%20of%20papers%20of%20every%20examination%20in%20UP%20was%20not%20only%20a%20proof%20of%20the%20corruption%20prevalent%20in%20the%20BJP%20government%20but%20what%20was%20more%20serious%20was%20the%20careless%20and%20misleading%20attitude%20of%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdityanath%20has%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20will%20be%20no%20compromise%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20sanctity%20of%20the%20examinations.%20%E2%80%9CThose%20playing%20with%20the%20hard%20work%20of%20the%20youth%20will%20not%20be%20spared%20under%20any%20cost%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708783619000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F24193316%2Fimage-1874.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fup-police-recruitment-exam-cancelled-bjp-yields-to-pressure-amid-paper-leak-allegations-protests%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20initially%20denying%20the%20allegations%20of%20a%20paper%20leak%2C%20the%20UP%20home%20department%2C%20under%20chief%20minister%20Adityanath%2C%20on%20Saturday%20afternoon%2C%20said%20it%20had%20directed%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Police%20Recruitment%20and%20Promotion%20Board%20to%20conduct%20fresh%20exams%20within%20six%20months.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fup-police-recruitment-exam-cancelled-bjp-yields-to-pressure-amid-paper-leak-allegations-protests%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Progress'%20in%20hostage%20talks%20as%20Hamas%20'drops'%20some%20of%20its%20demands%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708783380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F02%2F70x70%2Fskynews-israel-gaza-palestinian_6466497.jpg%3F20240223133900%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsignificant-progress-in-paris-hostage-talks-israeli-media-13079851%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Bprogress%26quot%3B%20in%20talks%20on%20a%20hostage%20deal%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%20in%20Paris%20after%20the%20group%20%26quot%3Bdropped%20some%20of%20its%20demands%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A404%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsignificant-progress-in-paris-hostage-talks-israeli-media-13079851%