%7C%205.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fwatch-indians-episode-5-nalanda-and-the-decline-of-buddhism%5C%22%3ENalanda%20and%20the%20Decline%20of%20Buddhism%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%206.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fwatch-indians-episode-6-khajuraho-and-the-world-of-tantra%5C%22%3EKhajuraho%20and%20the%20World%20of%20Tantra%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%207.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fwatch-indians-episode-7-alberuni-and-marco-polo-in-india%5C%22%3EAlberuni%20and%20Marco%20Polo%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Vijayanagar%20Empire%20(1336%E2%80%931565)%20once%20ruled%20much%20of%20south%20India.%20Foreigners%20have%20left%20vivid%20accounts%20of%20its%20capital%20city%2C%20aka%20Vijayanagar%E2%80%94its%20grand%20temples%2C%20palaces%2C%20royal%20baths%2C%20audience%20halls%2C%20Islamic%20quarter%2C%20bazaars%2C%20military%20might%2C%20and%20cosmopolitanism.%20Considered%20the%20birthplace%20of%20Carnatic%20music%2C%20Vijayanagar%20also%20evolved%20syncretic%20forms%20of%20architecture%2C%20governance%2C%20and%20courtly%20attire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFolk%20tales%20abound%20of%20its%20famous%20king%2C%20Krishnadevaraya%2C%20and%20his%20minister%2C%20Tenali%20Raman%2C%20who%20had%20a%20clever%20solution%20to%20every%20problem.%20The%20city%E2%80%99s%20remains%20now%20lie%20near%20Hampi%20village%2C%20in%20a%20beautiful%20rocky%20landscape%20by%20the%20Tungabhadra%20River.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20did%20Vijayanagar%20acquire%20all%20the%20wealth%20that%20impressed%20foreign%20travellers%3F%20Their%20eyewitness%20accounts%20%E2%80%93%20and%20contemporary%20scholars%20%E2%80%93%20reveal%20much%20about%20its%20economy%2C%20social%20customs%2C%20big%20festivals%2C%20and%20the%20cloistered%20lives%20of%20its%20elite%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20episode%2C%20Namit%20Arora%20describes%20what%E2%80%99s%20known%20about%20its%20trade%2C%20taxation%2C%20governance%2C%20policing%2C%20crime%20and%20punishment.%20He%20also%20looks%20at%20Vijayanagar%E2%80%99s%20religious%20landscape%20and%20courtly%20norms%2C%20its%20eager%20embrace%20of%20Persianate%20culture%2C%20and%20its%20war%20machine%20and%20shifting%20military%20alliances%20in%20which%20religion%20mattered%20little.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20finally%2C%20the%20causes%20of%20the%20empire%E2%80%99s%20massive%20defeat%20at%20the%20battle%20of%20Talikota.%20Hindu%20nationalists%20today%20fondly%20imagine%20Vijayanagar%20as%20a%20self-conscious%20bastion%20of%20Hinduism%20bravely%20resisting%20the%20%E2%80%98onslaught%20of%20Islam%E2%80%99.%20Is%20that%20true%3F%20As%20we%E2%80%99ll%20see%2C%20history%20is%20messy%2C%20and%20it%20often%20confounds%20sectarian%20readings%20of%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FswZe7svYNDw%3Fsi%3DzwrxflUJDasGyg3N%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBelow%20is%20the%20full%20transcript%20of%20the%20episode.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHello%20and%20welcome%20to%20Indians.%20I%E2%80%99m%20Namit%20Arora.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20previous%20episode%2C%20we%20looked%20at%20medieval%20India%20through%20the%20accounts%20of%20two%20famous%20travellers%2C%20Alberuni%20and%20Marco%20Polo.%20After%20Marco%20Polo%E2%80%99s%20departure%2C%20a%20series%20of%20wars%20reorganised%20the%20fragmented%20political%20map%20of%20south%20India%20into%20two%20entities%3A%20The%20Bahmani%20Sultanate%20and%20the%20Vijayanagar%20Empire.%20In%20this%20episode%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20look%20at%20the%20rise%20and%20fall%20of%20the%20Vijayanagar%20Empire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20own%20fascination%20for%20Vijayanagar%20began%20as%20a%20kid%2C%20when%20I%20first%20read%20the%20stories%20of%20its%20famous%20king%20Krishnadevaraya%2C%20and%20his%20minister%2C%20Tenali%20Raman%2C%20who%20had%20a%20clever%20solution%20to%20every%20problem.%20He%20seemed%20to%20always%20outsmart%20the%20crooks%20and%20save%20the%20day%2C%20while%20imparting%20a%20sort%20of%20chaloo%20%5B%E0%A4%9A%E0%A4%BE%E0%A4%B2%E0%A5%82%5D%20wisdom.%20In%20stories%2C%20they%20were%20the%20south%20Indian%20counterparts%20to%20Akbar%20and%20Birbal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20its%20peak%2C%20the%20Vijayanagar%20Empire%20covered%20much%20of%20south%20India.%20Many%20foreign%20travellers%20have%20left%20behind%20vivid%20accounts%20of%20its%20wealth%2C%20military%20power%2C%20and%20its%20cosmopolitan%20society%20and%20culture.%20It%20innovated%20new%20and%20syncretic%20forms%20of%20architecture%2C%20governance%2C%20and%20courtly%20norms%2C%20and%20was%20the%20birthplace%20of%20Carnatic%20music.%20Many%20Hindu%20nationalists%20today%20fondly%20imagine%20Vijayanagar%20as%20a%20proud%20Hindu%20kingdom%20that%20bravely%20resisted%20the%20%E2%80%98onslaught%20of%20Islam%E2%80%99.%20Is%20that%20true%3F%20As%20we%E2%80%99ll%20see%2C%20history%20is%20messy%2C%20and%20it%20often%20confounds%20sectarian%20readings%20of%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHampi%E2%80%99s%20physical%20geography%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20possible%20that%20because%20of%20the%20stories%20I%20had%20heard%20as%20a%20child%2C%20I%20was%20primed%20to%20fall%20in%20love%20with%20the%20magnificent%2C%20sprawling%20ruins%20of%20the%20city%20of%20Vijayanagar%2C%20which%20was%20the%20capital%20of%20the%20Vijayanagar%20Empire.%20Once%20the%20political%2C%20religious%2C%20and%20commercial%20hub%20of%20a%20large%20empire%2C%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20remains%20now%20lie%20near%20the%20town%20of%20Hampi%2C%20in%20a%20beautiful%20rocky%20landscape%20just%20south%20of%20the%20meandering%20Tunghabhadra%20River.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20its%20ruined%20state%2C%20the%20city%20of%20Vijayanagar%20is%20overwhelming.%20Spread%20over%2030%20sq.%20km%2C%20we%20can%20make%20out%20two%20major%20zones%3A%20a%20northern%20%E2%80%98Sacred%20Centre%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20a%20southern%20%E2%80%98Urban%20Core%E2%80%99.%20The%20Sacred%20Centre%20abounds%20in%20temples%20and%20shrines%2C%20which%20include%20the%20Virupaksha%20Temple%2C%20Vitthala%20Temple%2C%20Krishna%20Temple%2C%20and%20Achyutaraya%20Temple.%20Many%20of%20them%20are%20adjacent%20to%20former%20bazaars%20lining%20long%20streets%2C%20hosting%20single%20and%20double-storied%20shops%20and%20pavilions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Urban%20Core%20is%20where%20the%20elites%20lived%3B%20it%20had%20palaces%2C%20royal%20baths%2C%20audience%20halls%2C%20and%20homes%20made%20of%20stone.%20This%20elite%20area%20had%20many%20thick%20walls%2C%20gateways%2C%20and%20watchtowers%E2%80%94a%20defensive%20response%20to%20the%20perennial%20threat%20of%20war%20and%20internal%20rebellion.%20The%20common%20folk%20lived%20outside%20these%20two%20zones%2C%20in%20homes%20made%20of%20perishable%20materials.%20Between%20and%20beyond%20the%20two%20zones%20were%20agricultural%20fields%2C%20which%20were%20fed%20by%20canals%20like%20this%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHampi%E2%80%99s%20sacred%20geography%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20area%20around%20Hampi%2C%20prehistoric%20settlements%20and%20burial%20sites%20go%20back%20at%20least%203000%20years.%20Hampi%20is%20an%20important%20site%20in%20the%20Ramayana.%20Known%20in%20the%20tales%20as%20Kishkindha%2C%20it%20is%20home%20to%20the%20vanara%20(or%20%E2%80%98monkey%E2%80%99)%20kingdom%20of%20Vali%2C%20Sugriva%2C%20and%20Hanuman.%20It%20was%20above%20Kishkindha%20that%20Sita%20dropped%20her%20jewels%20as%20Ravana%20flew%20her%20away%20to%20Lanka.%20Local%20lore%20has%20cooked%20up%20an%20elaborate%20schema%20of%20Ramayana%20sites%20at%20Hampi%3A%20the%20pond%20by%20which%20Sita%E2%80%99s%20jewels%20fell%3B%20the%20cave%20where%20Sugriva%20hid%20them%3B%20the%20rocky%20ledge%20from%20where%20Rama%20fired%20the%20arrow%20to%20murder%20Vali.%20Hanuman%20was%20a%20big%20favourite%20with%20Vijayanagar%E2%80%99s%20sculptors%2C%20who%20depicted%20him%20with%20a%20raised%20hand%20and%20an%20overlarge%20tail.%20A%20shrine%20nearby%2C%20atop%20Anjeyanadri%20Hill%2C%20claims%20to%20be%20his%20birthplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%207th%20century%20CE%2C%20local%20tribal%20groups%20worshipped%20a%20powerful%20river%20goddess%2C%20called%20Pampa.%20From%20her%20name%20in%20Kannada%2C%20Hampe%2C%20we%20get%20Hampi.%20Pampa%E2%80%99s%20husband%2C%20Virupaskha%2C%20was%20a%20minor%20god.%20But%20through%20the%20process%20of%20Sanskritization%2C%20they%20were%20admitted%20into%20the%20Brahminical%20pantheon%20as%20forms%20of%20Parvati%20and%20Shiva%E2%80%94and%20their%20power%20got%20reversed.%20Pampa%20became%20a%20mere%20%E2%80%98consort%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20sidekick%2C%20to%20the%20more%20powerful%20Virupaksha.%20This%20power%20reversal%20is%20of%20course%20a%20common%20story%20among%20folk%20gods%20across%20the%20subcontinent.%20By%20the%2012th%20century%2C%20a%20temple%20to%20them%20had%20appeared%20at%20Hampi%2C%20which%20would%20become%20a%20foundational%20site%20and%20institution%20of%20Vijayanagar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESouth%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20transformation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%2013th%20century%2C%20south%20India%20was%20a%20patchwork%20of%20warring%20kingdoms%20with%20shifting%20borders.%20These%20kingdoms%20were%20of%20two%20kinds%3A%20the%20first%20were%20the%20wealthier%20kingdoms%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Cholas%20and%20Pandyas%2C%20situated%20in%20fertile%20coastal%20river%20basins%E2%80%94which%20Marco%20Polo%20had%20written%20about.%20The%20second%20kind%20were%20located%20in%20the%20arid%20peninsular%20uplands%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Kakatiyas%2C%20Hoysalas%2C%20and%2C%20later%2C%20Vijayanagar.%20They%20had%20a%20weaker%20economic%20base%20and%20tended%20to%20be%20more%20warlike.%20This%20natural%20asymmetry%20doomed%20the%20coastal%20states%20to%20political%20subordination%20and%20plunder%20from%20raids%20by%20the%20upland%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20political%20map%20was%20shaken%20up%20by%20a%20new%20expansionary%20force%20in%20the%20early%2014th%20century%3A%20the%20Delhi%20Sultanate%2C%20led%20by%20Ala-ud-Din%20Khalji%20and%20Muhammad%20bin%20Tughlak.%20They%20commanded%20greater%20military%20discipline%2C%20meritocracy%2C%20and%20battlefield%20innovations.%20They%20were%20simply%20better%20at%20the%20game%20of%20conquest%20and%20domination%20that%20Indian%20rulers%20also%20played.%20Their%20cavalry-led%20armies%20were%20more%20formidable%20than%20anything%20the%20southern%20rulers%20had%20faced%20before.%20Great%20battles%20led%20to%20the%20rise%20and%20fall%20of%20many%20kingdoms.%20South%20Indians%20were%20forced%20to%20raise%20their%20military%20game%2C%20especially%20the%20founders%20of%20Vijayanagar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20dust%20settled%20in%20the%20mid-14th%20century%2C%20a%20sovereign%20Muslim%20kingdom%20had%20arisen%20in%20the%20mid-peninsula.%20It%20was%20founded%20by%20Bahman%20Shah%2C%20formerly%20a%20rebellious%20general%20in%20Tughlak%E2%80%99s%20army.%20The%20Bahmani%20Sultanate%20patronised%20Islam%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Persian%20language%20and%20culture%20in%20its%20urban%20centres.%20Within%20a%20few%20generations%2C%20the%20Deccani%20dialect%20of%20Urdu%20would%20become%20the%20lingua%20franca%20of%20the%20ruling%20class%2C%20which%20included%20many%20Hindus.%20Sufi%20orders%20gained%20popularity%20and%20many%20lower-caste%20Hindus%20voluntarily%20converted%20to%20Islam.%20As%20with%20most%20new%20political%20dynasties%2C%20the%20Bahmani%20Sultanate%20caused%20disruptions%20for%20some%20social%20groups%2C%20while%20creating%20new%20opportunities%20for%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20its%20south%20emerged%20the%20powerful%20Vijayanagar%20Empire.%20It%20was%20founded%20by%20two%20soldier-brothers%2C%20Hakka%20and%20Bukka%2C%20who%20were%20Shudras%20and%20likely%20Telugus.%20In%20c.%201336%2C%20the%20brothers%20established%20their%20capital%20at%20Hampi.%20They%20fought%20against%20the%20Bahmani%20Sultanate%20as%20well%20as%20other%20Hindu%20kingdoms%20of%20the%20south.%20They%20were%20able%20to%20grow%20their%20domains%20because%20they%20were%20no%20less%20militaristic%20and%20violent%20than%20the%20Bahmani%20sultans.%20In%20a%20few%20decades%2C%20the%20Vijayanagar%20kings%20controlled%20much%20of%20the%20region%20south%20of%20the%20Krishna%20River%2C%20ruling%2025%20million%20people%2C%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20whole%20subcontinent%20had%20around%20125%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20foreign%20travellers%20saw%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20fair%20bit%20of%20our%20knowledge%20about%20Vijayanagar%20comes%20from%20the%20accounts%20of%20foreign%20travellers%20of%20the%2015th%20and%2016th%20centuries%2C%20such%20as%20Niccol%C3%B2%20de%E2%80%99%20Conti%2C%20a%20Venetian%20merchant%20(1420)%3B%20Abdur%20Razzaq%2C%20a%20Persian%20scholar-envoy%20(1443)%3B%20Duarte%20Barbosa%2C%20a%20Portuguese%20officer%20(c.%201515)%3B%20and%20two%20Portuguese%20merchant-adventurers%2C%20Domingo%20Paes%20(c.%201520)%20and%20Fern%C3%A3o%20Nuniz%20(1535%E2%80%9337).%20Their%20accounts%20offer%20a%20vivid%20sense%20of%20Vijayanagar%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20class%20and%20courtly%20culture%2C%20its%20economy%20and%20trade%2C%20religion%20and%20politics%2C%20public%20customs%20and%20festivals%2C%20and%20much%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20common%20themes%20emerge%20from%20their%20accounts.%20Many%20of%20them%20speak%20of%20Vijayanagar%20as%20a%20dazzling%20city%E2%80%94of%20orchards%2C%20gardens%2C%20grand%20temples%2C%20palaces%2C%20baths%2C%20water%20tanks%20and%20lakes.%20They%20speak%20of%20merchants%20and%20wealthy%20men%20in%20the%20city%2C%20including%20visitors%20who%20might%20be%20%E2%80%98Christian%2C%20Jew%2C%20Moor%20or%20Heathen%E2%80%99.%20There%20was%20even%20an%20Islamic%20quarter%20with%20mosques%20and%20tombs.%20They%20speak%20of%20shops%20and%20bazaars%20on%20wide%20streets%20near%20major%20temples%2C%20overflowing%20with%20precious%20goods%20like%20pearls%20and%20diamonds%2C%20leather%20shoes%20embroidered%20in%20silk%2C%20vermilion%2C%20opium%2C%20grooming%20products%20for%20fashionable%20men%20and%20women%2C%20scented%20materials%2C%20pepper%2C%20fine%20textiles%20and%20cheaper%20brocades%20from%20China%20and%20Alexandria%20in%20Egypt.%20The%20city%E2%80%99s%20population%20topped%20250%2C000%2C%20making%20it%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20in%20the%20world.%20It%20was%20a%20cosmopolitan%20city%2C%20whose%20public%20art%20and%20temple%20walls%20even%20had%20whimsical%20carvings%20of%20foreign%20travellers%20in%20their%20native%20attires%E2%80%94hard%20to%20imagine%20on%20modern%20temples%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20travellers%20also%20describe%20the%20great%20fanfare%20with%20which%20people%20celebrated%20festivals.%20Dussehra%20was%20the%20biggest%2C%20involving%209%20days%20of%20feasting%2C%20dancing%2C%20circus%20acts%2C%20wrestling%2C%20games%2C%20fireworks%2C%20even%20a%20public%20slaughter%20of%20buffaloes.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20it%20came%20military%20parades%2C%20which%20were%20a%20great%20testosterone-driven%20display%20of%20the%20king%E2%80%99s%20military%20might%2C%20meant%20to%20impress%20both%20his%20subjects%20and%20his%20enemies.%20Much%20like%20our%20display%20of%20missiles%20and%20fighter%20jets%20in%20Delhi%20on%20Republic%20Day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDomingo%20Paes%20found%20Vijayanagar%E2%80%99s%20markets%20well%20stocked%20with%20grains%2C%20pulses%2C%20butter%2C%20oil%2C%20milk%3B%20fruits%20like%20mangoes%2C%20oranges%2C%20lime%2C%20pomegranates%2C%20jackfruit%20and%20grapes%3B%20vegetables%20like%20brinjals%20and%20radishes.%20Nuniz%20wrote%20that%20people%20%E2%80%98eat%20mutton%2C%20pork%2C%20venison%2C%20partridges%2C%20hares%2C%20doves%2C%20quail%20and%20all%20kinds%20of%20birds%3B%20even%20sparrows%20and%20rats%2C%20and%20cats%20and%20lizards%2C%20all%20of%20which%20are%20sold%20in%20the%20%5Bcity%E2%80%99s%5D%20market%E2%80%99.%20Since%20then%2C%20religious%20ideas%20and%20tastes%20have%20changed%20so%20much%20that%20today%2C%20meat%20is%20banned%20in%20Hampi%20village.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPaes%20met%20king%20Krishnadevaraya%20in%20the%201520s.%20Paes%20calls%20him%20%E2%80%98the%20most%20feared%20and%20perfect%20king%E2%80%99%2C%20who%20begins%20his%20day%20with%20a%20drink%20of%20seed%20oil%2C%20rubs%20it%20on%20his%20body%20and%20does%20weightlifting%2C%20wrestling%2C%20fencing%20and%20horse%20riding.%20Then%20he%20is%20bathed%20by%20a%20Brahmin%2C%20after%20which%20the%20king%20does%20puja%20and%20begins%20his%20courtly%20duties.%20Near%20his%20palace%20is%20a%20temple%20where%20they%20sacrifice%20%E2%80%98every%20day%20many%20sheep%E2%80%99.%20The%20travellers%20document%20all%20sorts%20of%20royal%20intrigues%2C%20assassinations%20and%20intra-family%20violence%20in%20Vijayanagar.%20Men%20of%20the%20royal%20family%20often%20killed%20each%20other%2C%20and%20paranoia%20was%20commonplace.%20All%20these%20have%20long%20been%20occupational%20hazards%20in%20dynasties%20around%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20culture%20of%20vijayanagar%E2%80%99s%20elites%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20language%20of%20the%20Vijayanagar%20court%20was%20Telugu.%20Kannada%20and%20Sanskrit%20were%20common%20too.%20The%20same%20Krishnadevaraya%20who%20led%20violent%20military%20campaigns%2C%20was%20also%20a%20patron%20of%20the%20arts%20and%20literature.%20He%20supported%20eight%20great%20poets%20in%20his%20court%2C%20including%20Allasani%20Peddana%2C%20often%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98grandfather%20of%20Telugu%20poetry%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20Tenali%20Raman%2C%20who%20was%20a%20poet%2C%20scholar%2C%20court%20jester%2C%20and%20the%20hero%20of%20many%20a%20folk%20story%20I%20read%20as%20a%20child%20in%20north%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20class%20of%20Vijayanagar%20was%20almost%20entirely%20Hindu%2C%20but%20which%20strands%20of%20Hinduism%20did%20it%20patronise%3F%20Both%20Vaishnava%20and%20Shaiva.%20It%20supported%20both%20Vedantic%20non-dualism%20and%20dualism%2C%20that%20is%2C%20both%20Adi%20Shankara%E2%80%99s%20Brahminism%2C%20as%20well%20as%20Bhakti%20devotionalism.%20Among%20the%20latter%20was%20a%20Bhakti%20saint%20called%20Purandara%20Dasa%20(1484%E2%80%931564).%20He%20composed%20and%20sang%20devotional%20melodies%20to%20Lord%20Vitthala%20and%20lived%20in%20this%20airy%20mandapa%20by%20the%20river.%20Today%2C%20this%20scholar-saint%20from%20Vijayanagar%20is%20widely%20regarded%20as%20the%20father%20of%20Carnatic%20music.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20untouchable%20groups%20existed%20in%20Vijayanagar%2C%20along%20with%20bonded%20slaves.%20As%20always%2C%20their%20unwritten%20experiences%20are%20harder%20to%20recover.%20One%20exception%20is%20the%20Bhakti%20saint%20Kanaka%20Dasa%2C%20a%20shepherd%2C%20who%20was%20denied%20entry%20into%20Hindu%20temples.%20His%20songs%20poetically%20lamented%20the%20caste%20order%20that%20marked%20and%20constrained%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20perceptive%20observer%20might%20notice%20how%20little%20erotica%20there%20is%20on%20temple%20walls%20in%20Vijayanagar.%20In%20the%20episode%20on%20Khajuraho%2C%20we%20looked%20at%20how%20Hinduism%20had%20started%20becoming%20more%20orthodox%2C%20puritanical%2C%20and%20patriarchal%20centuries%20before%20the%20rise%20of%20Turko-Persian%20rule.%20Vijayanagar%20was%20part%20of%20this%20journey%20towards%20the%20conservative%20strains%20of%20Hinduism%20and%20temple%20art%20that%20we%20have%20today.%20So%20the%20little%20erotica%20it%20does%20have%20is%20more%20like%20an%20afterthought.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20while%20Vijayanagar%E2%80%99s%20elites%20were%20Hindu%2C%20their%20material%20and%20political%20culture%20had%20been%20significantly%20Persianized%2C%20including%20their%20courtly%20attire%3A%20the%20%3Cem%3Ekabayi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20long-sleeved%20pullover%20tunic%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Ekullayi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20high%2C%20brimless%20conical%20cap.%20This%20differed%20sharply%20from%20the%20loincloth-wearing%20Hindu%20kings%20more%20typical%20of%20south%20India.%20Persianate%20attire%20probably%20raised%20their%20status%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20the%20envoys%20and%20traders%20of%20all%20Muslim%20kingdoms%2C%20because%20Persianate%20norms%20then%20signified%20high%20culture%20both%20in%20West%20Asia%20and%20South%20Asia.%20This%20embrace%20was%20voluntary%2C%20and%20is%20also%20evident%20in%20other%20realms%20in%20Vijayanagar%2C%20such%20as%20its%20Persianate%20architecture%2C%20administration%2C%20military%20technology%2C%20and%20more.%20Vijayanagar%E2%80%99s%20kings%20also%20patronised%20Islam%20in%20their%20domains%20and%20hired%20Muslim%20nobles%20in%20their%20courts.%20In%20short%2C%20their%20elites%20valued%20Persianate%20culture%20and%20happily%20embraced%20it%20in%20multiple%20arenas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20lives%20of%20upper-class%20women%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20kings%20of%20Vijayanagar%20kept%20large%20harems%2C%20for%20which%20%E2%80%98the%20fairest%20and%20healthiest%20women%20are%20sought%20throughout%20the%20kingdom%E2%80%99%2C%20wrote%20the%20Portuguese%20traveller%20Duarte%20Barbosa.%20Once%20chosen%2C%20the%20women%20were%20materially%20secure%20for%20life%20but%20they%20%E2%80%98are%20never%20seen%20by%20any%20%5Bunapproved%5D%20man%20.%20.%20.%20When%20they%20wish%20to%20go%20out%2C%20they%20are%20carried%20in%20litters%20shut%20up%20and%20closed%E2%80%99%2C%20accompanied%20by%20eunuchs.%20%E2%80%98They%20bathe%20daily%20in%20the%20many%20tanks%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98king%20goes%20to%20see%20them%20bathing%2C%20and%20she%20who%20pleases%20him%20most%20is%20asked%20to%20come%20to%20his%20chamber%E2%80%99.%20Barbosa%20claimed%20that%20%E2%80%98there%20is%20such%20envy%20and%20rivalry%20among%20these%20women%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20king%E2%80%99s%20favour%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Csome%20kill%20others%E2%80%9D%20and%20some%20poison%20themselves%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20picture%20that%20emerges%20from%20multiple%20testimonies%20is%20that%20most%20queens%20and%20concubines%20of%20Vijayanagar%20led%20miserable%20lives%2C%20as%20if%20combining%20the%20worst%20of%20Hindu%20and%20Islamic%20patriarchy.%20They%20were%20segregated%20and%20confined%20indoors%2C%20guarded%20by%20eunuchs.%20They%20learned%20many%20arts%20in%20their%20walled%20gardens%20but%20were%20given%20no%20public%20role.%20When%20the%20king%20died%2C%20they%20were%20expected%20to%20commit%20sati%2C%20though%20this%20was%20not%20always%20realised.%20Widows%20of%20Kshatriya%20men%20who%20refused%20sati%20were%20held%20%E2%80%98in%20great%20dishonour%20%E2%80%A6%20and%20a%20shame%20to%20their%20families%E2%80%99%2C%20wrote%20Barbosa.%20If%20young%2C%20they%20were%20sent%20to%20a%20temple%20%E2%80%98to%20earn%20money%20for%20it%20with%20their%20bodies%E2%80%99.%20Women%20of%20other%20classes%20suffered%20none%20of%20these%20indignities%20and%20led%20freer%20lives%2C%20though%20still%20subject%20to%20the%20common%20norms%20of%20patriarchy%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20how%20did%20most%20kings%20of%20Vijayanagar%20die%3F%20Not%20on%20the%20military%20battlefield%2C%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20but%20on%20the%20sexual%20battlefield.%20According%20to%20Nuniz%2C%20Krishnadevaraya%20died%20%E2%80%98of%20the%20same%20illness%20of%20which%20all%20of%20his%20ancestors%20had%20died%2C%20with%20pains%20in%20the%20groin%2C%20of%20which%20die%20all%20the%20kings%20of%20Vijayanagar%E2%80%99.%20This%20sounds%20like%20venereal%20disease%E2%80%94hardly%20surprising%2C%20given%20their%20extreme%20promiscuity.%20Of%20course%2C%20this%20would%20have%20meant%20that%20the%20same%20death%20stalked%20many%20women%20of%20the%20harem%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFemale%20prostitution%20was%20legal.%20Taxes%20from%20sex%20workers%20paid%20for%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20police%20services%2C%20claimed%20the%20Persian%20traveller%20Abdur%20Razzaq.%20The%20prostitutes%2C%20he%20wrote%2C%20wear%20%E2%80%98costly%20pearls%20and%20jewels%20and%20fine%20clothing%2C%20are%20quite%20young%20and%20extremely%20beautiful%2C%20and%20with%20each%20stand%20one%20or%20two%20serving%20girls%E2%80%99.%20They%20ply%20their%20trade%20on%20attractive%20streets%2C%20waiting%20for%20customers%20on%20chairs%20outside%20rows%20of%20chambers%2C%20%E2%80%98as%20clean%20as%20can%20be%E2%80%99.%20Some%20temples%20kept%20devadasis%2C%20who%2C%20like%20the%20courtesans%20of%20the%20elite%2C%20traded%20sexual%20favours%20for%20money.%20The%20state%20also%20hired%20thousands%20of%20prostitutes%20to%20accompany%20the%20army%20on%20its%20long%20military%20campaigns.%20Far%20from%20merely%20tolerating%20and%20legalising%20it%2C%20the%20state%20of%20Vijayanagar%20actively%20recruited%20young%20women%20into%20prostitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECrime%20and%20punishment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolicing%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Vijayanagar%20was%20efficient%2C%20and%20punishments%20were%2C%20well%2C%20very%20medieval.%20Small-time%20thieves%20had%20a%20foot%20and%20a%20hand%20cut%20off%2C%20wrote%20Nuniz.%20Major%20thieves%2C%20and%20also%20rapists%2C%20were%20hung%20by%20a%20hook%20piercing%20their%20chin.%20Traitors%20were%20%E2%80%98impaled%20alive%20on%20a%20wooden%20stake%20thrust%20through%20the%20belly%20%E2%80%A6%20people%20of%20the%20lower%20orders%2C%20for%20whatever%20crime%20they%20commit%E2%80%99%20had%20their%20heads%20cut%20off%20in%20the%20market-place.%20Occasionally%2C%20the%20king%20had%20a%20man%20thrown%20to%20the%20elephants%2C%20who%20tore%20him%20to%20pieces.%20Nuniz%20reported%20all%20this%20in%20a%20matter-of-fact%20way%2C%20perhaps%20because%20Vijayanagar%20was%20hardly%20exceptional%E2%80%94medieval%20European%20states%20also%20doled%20out%20appallingly%20cruel%20punishments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECuriously%2C%20one%20crime%20that%20was%20tolerated%20in%20Vijayanagar%20was%20bribery.%20Public%20officials%20at%20all%20levels%20expected%20bribes%20from%20traders.%20Nuniz%2C%20a%20horse%20trader%20himself%2C%20wrote%20that%20%E2%80%98You%20must%20perforce%20pay%20bribes%20to%20all%20the%20several%20officers%20with%20whom%20you%20have%20to%20deal.%20They%20will%20do%20nothing%20without%20some%20profit%20to%20themselves.%E2%80%99%20Here%E2%80%99s%20another%20example%20of%20a%20cultural%20habit%20with%20deep%20roots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20law%20of%20the%20land%20was%20not%20only%20harsher%20against%20the%20%E2%80%98lower%20orders%2C%E2%80%99%20it%20was%20markedly%20gentler%20on%20the%20upper-castes.%20According%20to%20Barbosa%2C%20men%20of%20the%20priestly%20class%20%E2%80%98hold%20the%20greatest%20liberties%20and%20privileges%20and%20are%20not%20liable%20to%20death%E2%80%99%20for%20any%20crime.%20They%20receive%20%E2%80%98much%20alms%E2%80%99.%20Some%20priests%20%E2%80%98have%20estates%20while%20others%20live%20in%20%5Bmonasteries%20with%5D%20good%20revenues.%20Some%20are%20great%20eaters%20and%20never%20work%20except%20to%20feed%20well%E2%80%99%2C%20wrote%20Barbosa.%20Most%20travellers%20saw%20Brahmins%20as%20a%20prosperous%20group%2C%20who%20were%20often%20administrators%2C%20merchants%2C%20and%20landowners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20political%20economy%20of%20Vijayanagar%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20how%20did%20the%20city%20of%20Vijayanagar%20acquire%20all%20the%20wealth%20that%20impressed%20foreign%20travellers%3F%20The%20first%20thing%20to%20recognize%20is%20that%20Vijayanagar%20Empire%20was%20an%20imperial%20state%20run%20by%20warrior-chiefs.%20They%20had%20conquered%20the%20economically%20productive%20regions%20of%20south%20India%20through%20brute%20force%2C%20including%20coastal%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20Andhra%20Pradesh.%20They%20kept%20a%20large%20standing%20army%20whose%20ranks%20included%20thousands%20of%20Turkish%20and%20Indian%20Muslims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20what%20was%20sold%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Vijayanagar%20came%20from%20outside%2C%20arriving%20on%20about%202%2C000%20bullock%20carts%20daily.%20The%20goods%20were%20taxed%20at%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20gates%20like%20this%20one.%20But%20land%20use%20tax%20was%20the%20largest%20source%20of%20revenue%20for%20the%20state.%20Other%20key%20taxpayers%20included%20traders%2C%20merchants%2C%20and%20producers%20of%20manufactured%20goods.%20Taxes%20also%20came%20from%20their%20many%20ports%20on%20the%20Malabar%20and%20Coromandel%20coasts.%20Foreign%20imports%20included%2013%2C000%20Arabian%20horses%20for%20the%20army%20each%20year.%20Military%20guards%20ensured%20the%20smooth%20flow%20of%20supplies%20on%20roads%20linking%20the%20ports%20to%20the%20capital.%20The%20Vijayanagar%20regime%20exerted%20its%20power%20and%20control%20through%20a%20cadre%20of%20regional%20governors%2C%20or%20nayaks.%20These%20were%20trusted%20royal%20kin%2C%20noblemen%20and%20warlords.%20They%20were%20often%20placed%20as%20outsiders%20to%20the%20districts%20they%20administered%E2%80%94say%2C%20Telugus%20or%20Kannadigas%20were%20sent%20to%20serve%20in%20Tamil%20country.%20There%20they%20asserted%20the%20king%E2%80%99s%20authority%20and%20collected%20rents.%20These%20governors%20resided%20in%20fortified%20garrisons%2C%20from%20where%20they%20maintained%20standing%20armies%20to%20quell%20local%20rebellions%20and%20joined%20the%20Vijayanagar%20army%20when%20summoned.%20It%20was%20very%20much%20a%20feudal%20arrangement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20city%20of%20Vijayanagar%20was%20the%20capital%20of%20an%20imperial%20war%20state%2C%20sustained%20by%20military%20force%20and%20%E2%80%98courtly%20patronage%2C%20to%20which%20much%20of%20the%20wealth%20of%20the%20empire%20was%20diverted%E2%80%99.%20And%20this%20wealth%20is%20what%20foreign%20travellers%20saw%20and%20reported%20in%20its%20capital%E2%80%94wealth%20that%20was%20extracted%20from%20the%20subjugated%20people%20of%20the%20empire.%20In%20this%20aspect%2C%20the%20Vijayanagar%20Empire%20was%20not%20fundamentally%20different%20from%20any%20other%20empire%20of%20its%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20fall%20of%20Vijayanagar%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20fascinating%20how%20and%20why%20the%20Vijayanagar%20Empire%20ended.%20In%201520%2C%20the%20Bahmani%20Sultanate%20broke%20up%20into%20five%20sultanates.%20In%20subsequent%20decades%2C%20all%20five%20were%20in%20shifting%20alliances%20and%20conflicts%20with%20each%20other%20and%20with%20Vijayanagar.%20They%20fought%20many%20battles%20for%20the%20control%20of%20the%20fertile%20Raichur%20doab.%20Muslims%20fought%20each%20other%3B%20Hindus%20fought%20each%20other%3B%20Hindus%20allied%20with%20Muslims%20to%20fight%20Hindus%3B%20Muslims%20allied%20with%20Hindus%20to%20fight%20Muslims.%20For%20example%2C%20Vijayanagar%20often%20allied%20with%20some%20sultanates%20against%20others%2C%20but%20its%20most%20hated%20rival%20was%20the%20Hindu%20Gajapati%20rulers%20of%20Odisha.%20We%20really%20see%20all%20permutations%20and%20combinations!%20In%20the%20realpolitik%20of%20both%20rajas%20and%20sultans%2C%20religion%20was%20much%20less%20a%20source%20of%20conflict%20than%20the%20demands%20of%20imperial%20power%20and%20economic%20self-interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20armies%20of%20the%20sultanates%20had%20Hindu%20soldiers%20and%20generals%2C%20just%20as%20Vijayanagar%E2%80%99s%20armies%20had%20Muslim%20and%20Christian%20soldiers%20and%20generals.%20Elite%20warriors%20enjoyed%20professional%20options%20far%20beyond%20religious%20considerations.%20In%20reality%2C%20a%20warrior%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98loyalty%20to%20family%2C%20faction%2C%20or%20paymaster%20counted%20for%20more%20than%20loyalty%20to%20land%2C%20religion%2C%20or%20ethnic%20group%E2%80%99%20(Richard%20Eaton).%20Consider%20the%20remarkable%20case%20of%20Rama%20Raya%2C%20a%20top%20military%20general%20of%20Vijayanagar%20and%20son-in-law%20of%20Krishnadevaraya.%20Earlier%20in%20his%20life%2C%20he%20had%20enlisted%20for%20three%20years%20in%20the%20service%20of%20the%20sultan%20of%20Golconda%20(Quli%20Qutb-ul-Mulk)%2C%20a%20great%20rival%20of%20Vijayanagar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sequence%20of%20events%20is%20complex%2C%20but%20after%20a%20series%20of%20misadventures%20later%20in%20his%20life%2C%20when%20Rama%20Raya%20was%20the%20de%20facto%20ruler%20of%20Vijayanagar%2C%20four%20of%20the%20five%20sultanates%20united%20against%20him%20in%20a%20decisive%20battle.%20A%20great%20war%20took%20place%20in%201565%20at%20Talikota.%20But%20Vijayanagar%E2%80%99s%20army%2C%20led%20by%20the%20overconfident%20Rama%20Raya%2C%20now%2080%20years%20old%2C%20had%20fallen%20behind%20in%20military%20technology%2C%20like%20field%20artillery.%20With%20such%20vulnerabilities%2C%20they%20were%20quickly%20routed.%20Scholars%20would%20later%20blame%20the%20arrogant%20follies%20of%20Rama%20Raya%20for%20the%20%E2%80%98disaster%E2%80%99%20of%20Talikota.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20news%20of%20their%20defeat%20reached%20their%20capital%2C%20the%20royal%20family%20promptly%20fled%20with%20hundreds%20of%20elephants%20loaded%20with%20gold%2C%20diamonds%2C%20and%20precious%20stones.%20Many%20others%20left%20the%20city%20with%20the%20little%20they%20could%20carry.%20But%20before%20the%20enemy%20forces%20arrived%20to%20take%20what%20remained%2C%20the%20neighbouring%20tribespeople%20looted%20the%20city.%20One%20wonders%20what%20sort%20of%20relations%20Vijayanagar%20had%20fostered%20with%20the%20surrounding%20tribes%20to%20invite%20such%20opportunism.%20The%20city%20was%20then%20plundered%20by%20the%20victorious%20troops%2C%20which%20included%20Hindus%20like%20the%20Marathas%20of%20Bijapur%20and%20Telugus%20of%20Golconda.%20Such%20plunder%20by%20the%20winning%20side%20was%20a%20common%20practice%20in%20those%20times%E2%80%94it%20was%20considered%20part%20of%20a%20soldier%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98package%20of%20incentives%E2%80%99.%20Just%20six%20years%20earlier%2C%20Vijayanagar%20and%20Bijapur%20had%20aligned%20to%20defeat%20and%20similarly%20plunder%20Golconda%20and%20Ahmadnagar%2C%20where%20Rama%20Raya%E2%80%99s%20troops%20had%20even%20destroyed%20mosques.%20However%2C%20through%20the%20plunder%20of%20Vijayanagar%2C%20its%20temples%20and%20their%20delicate%20statuary%20would%20survive%20remarkably%20intact%2C%20which%20visitors%20to%20Hampi%20and%20to%20local%20museums%20can%20see%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWas%20Vijayanagar%20a%20Hindu%20kingdom%20that%20bravely%20resisted%20the%20%E2%80%98onslaught%20of%20Islam%E2%80%99%2C%20as%20many%20Hindu%20nationalists%20allege%20today%3F%20That%E2%80%99s%20not%20what%20history%20tells%20us.%20There%20is%20little%20evidence%20that%20the%20rulers%20of%20Vijayanagar%20were%20defending%20Hinduism%20against%20Islam.%20Happily%20syncretic%2C%20they%20had%20embraced%20many%20Persianate%20cultural%20norms%3B%20they%20employed%20Muslim%20fighters%20and%20commanders.%20In%20its%20courtly%20rituals%2C%20taxation%2C%20and%20governance%2C%20Vijayanagar%20resembled%20the%20sultanates%20of%20Bijapur%20and%20Golconda%20more%20than%20the%20Hindu%20domains%20of%20Pallavas%20and%20Cholas.%20Vijayanagar%E2%80%99s%20rajas%2C%20or%20rayas%2C%20allied%20with%20the%20sultans%20as%20often%20as%20they%20opposed%20them.%20They%20were%20mainly%20defending%20their%20kingdom%20against%20other%20kingdoms%2C%20whether%20Muslim%20or%20Hindu%2C%20using%20both%20Muslim%20and%20Hindu%20allies.%20To%20see%20the%20Deccan%20as%20a%20binary%20between%20an%20%E2%80%98evil%E2%80%99%20Muslim%20north%20and%20a%20%E2%80%98good%E2%80%99%20Hindu%20south%20is%20a%20projection%20of%20modern%20passions%20and%20prejudices%20upon%20the%20past.%20It%20really%20distorts%20the%20actual%20historical%20experience%20of%20medieval%20South%20Indians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20year%20of%20the%20battle%20of%20Talikota%2C%20the%20alliance%20of%20the%20four%20sultanates%20collapsed%2C%20and%20they%20again%20became%20rivals.%20In%20the%20following%20century%2C%20the%20Mughal%20Empire%20would%20swallow%20them%20all.%20But%20many%20of%20the%20nayaks%2C%20or%20the%20regional%20governors%20of%20Vijayanagar%20Empire%2C%20set%20up%20independent%20kingdoms%20of%20their%20own%2C%20such%20as%20at%20Mysore%2C%20Tanjore%2C%20Gingee%2C%20and%20Madurai.%20The%20great%20city%20of%20Vijayanagar%20was%20abandoned%2C%20and%20was%20eventually%20covered%20by%20a%20forest%20where%20tigers%20roamed%20the%20ruins.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20next%20episode%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20go%20north%20and%20take%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20Indian%20society%20during%20the%20Mughal%20Empire%2C%20especially%20during%20the%20reign%20of%20Aurangzeb.%20Among%20other%20things%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20lean%20on%20the%20account%20of%20the%20perceptive%20French%20traveller%2C%20Fran%C3%A7ois%20Bernier%2C%20a%20medical%20doctor%20who%20worked%20for%20a%20nobleman%20in%20Aurangzeb%E2%80%99s%20court%20for%20many%20years.%20See%20you%20next%20time!%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708770698000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F24154024%2Fimage-1872.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fwatch-indians-episode-8-the-vijayanagar-empire%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20episode%20explores%20various%20aspects%20of%20the%20Vijayanagar%20empire%2C%20including%20trade%2C%20taxation%2C%20governance%2C%20policing%2C%20crime%2C%20punishment%2C%20religious%20landscape%2C%20courtly%20norms%2C%20embrace%20of%20Persianate%20culture%2C%20military%20alliances%2C%20and%20the%20reasons%20behind%20its%20significant%20defeat%20at%20the%20Battle%20of%20Talikota.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fwatch-indians-episode-8-the-vijayanagar-empire%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Farmers%20spoiling%20for%20a%20punch-up%20storm%20agricultural%20show%20as%20problems%20mount%20