cting%20the%20semiconductor%20industry.%20They%20have%20urged%20India%20to%20support%20a%20permanent%20ban%20on%20customs%20duties%20for%20cross-border%20digital%20transactions%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Findia%2Findias-stance-data-transfers-wto-spooks-chip-giants-2024-02-23%2F%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Council%20has%20also%20warned%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20stance%20will%20stifle%20its%20own%20chip%20design%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Council%20represents%20chip%20giants%20like%20Intel%2C%20Qualcomm%20and%20Nvidia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Fwhy-wto-is-not-an-appropriate-forum-for-negotiating-e-commerce-rules%5C%22%3EWhy%20WTO%20Is%20Not%20an%20Appropriate%20Forum%20for%20Negotiating%20E-commerce%20Rule%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20week%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EHindu%20BusinessLine%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Findia-unlikely-to-extend-moratorium-on-customs-duties-on-e-commerce%2Farticle67868118.ece%5C%22%3Equoted%20an%20official%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20saying%20that%20India%20is%20unlikely%20to%20extend%20the%20moratorium%20on%20the%20imposition%20of%20customs%20duties%20on%20electronic%20transmissions%20at%20the%20WTO%E2%80%99s%2013th%20Ministerial%20Conference%20(MC13)%2C%20as%20there%20is%20no%20consensus%20on%20its%20scope%20and%20it%20benefited%20mostly%20developed%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNew%20Delhi%20is%20not%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20further%20extension%20of%20the%20e-commerce%20moratorium.%20We%20are%20unlikely%20to%20do%20so%20at%20MC13.%20Those%20who%20demand%20the%20moratorium%20should%20tell%20us%20what%20its%20scope%20is%20and%20what%20all%20it%20covers.%20Only%20then%20we%20can%20decide%20if%20there%20is%20a%20need%2C%E2%80%9D%20an%20official%20close%20to%20the%20negotiations%20told%20%3Ci%3E%3C%2Fi%3Eth